**Comparison:**

The one with a threshold of 0.5 had the best overall error rate, with an overall error rate of 10%. It also had the best type 1 (false positive) error rate, it being 1.5%. The model with the threshold of 0.05 has the best type 2 (false negative) error rate of 14%, compared to 77% and 34% for 0.5 and 0.1 respectively. So as the threshold gets smaller, Type 1 error rates gets worse, but Type 2 gets better.

